# Write modes

## `df.write.mode(...)` — a directory-level check

- Spark only checks whether the **path exists** — it never opens the old files

## The four modes

- **`overwrite`** — delete existing files, then write new ones (total replacement)
- **`append`** — add new part-files; old files untouched → **can't dedupe** (double append = duplicates)
- **`ignore`** — do nothing, silently (no write, no error)
- **`error`** *(default)* — raise `AnalysisException: path already exists`

## For row-level updates

- Need a **transactional layer** — Delta Lake / Iceberg. Plain files have no row-level update.
